              "text": "# Bayes’ Theorem\n\nBayes’ theorem is a mathematical formula used to determine the conditional probability of an event based on prior knowledge of conditions that might be related to the event.\n\n*   **The Formula:**\n    P(A|B) = [P(B|A) * P(A)] / P(B)\n\n*   **P(A|B):** The **Posterior Probability**. This is the probability of event A occurring given that B is true.\n*   **P(B|A):** The **Likelihood**. This is the probability of event B occurring given that A is true.\n*   **P(A):** The **Prior Probability**. This is the initial probability of event A before any evidence is considered.\n*   **P(B):** The **Marginal Likelihood**. This is the total probability of event B occurring under all possible circumstances.\n\nIn simple terms, it allows you to update your beliefs about a hypothesis (A) as you encounter new evidence (B).",
